HEADWORD: Suppository
<hw>Sup*pos"i*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Suppositories</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
<ets>suppositorium</ets>, fr. L. <ets>suppositorius</ets> that is placed
underneath: cf. F. <ets>suppositoire</ets>. See
<er>Supposition</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A pill or bolus for
introduction into the rectum; esp., a cylinder or cone of medicated
cacao butter.</def>⟦br⟧
